{"lemma":"خافِيَةٌ","slug":"خافِيَةٌ","root":"خ.ف.#","root_slug":"خ-ف-_","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ف-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خافِيَة","root":"خفي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11153"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11153","headword_ar":"خَافِيَةٌ","root":"xfY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAniyapN","text_ar":"عَلَانِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning that it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of being unapparent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not apparent, covert, secret, private,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clandestine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"though explained in the TK (followed by Freytag) as an epithet applied to a man, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose actions are always covert"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafFA","text_ar":"خَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAfK","text_ar":"خَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single feather, of the feathers called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxawaAfiY","text_ar":"الخَوَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxawaAfiY","text_ar":"الخَوَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the feathers below the ten that are in the fore part of the wing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain feathers that are concealed when the bird contracts its wing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the four feathers that are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after those called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmanaAkib","text_ar":"المَنَاكِب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and next before those called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abaAhir","text_ar":"الاَبَاهِر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bhr","text_ar":"بهر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nkb","text_ar":"نكب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven feathers in the wing, after the seven foremost:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) but the people [generally] mention them as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or they are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the small feathers in the wing of a bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanojarN","text_ar":"خَنْجَرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivolu xaAfiyapi Aln~asori","text_ar":"مِثْلُ خَافِيَةِ النَّسْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dagger like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAfyp","text_ar":"خافية"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the vulture"},{"kind":"text","text":"], occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xnjr","text_ar":"خنجر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAfiyapu AlguraAbi","text_ar":"خَافِيَةُ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAfyp","text_ar":"خافية"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the crow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the pl. is [sometimes expressed by using the coll. gen. n., saying]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlguraAbi","text_ar":"الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAfiY","text_ar":"خَافِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxawaAfiY","text_ar":"الخَوَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-branches"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qilabap","text_ar":"قِلَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branches that grow forth from the heart of the tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) thus called in the dial. of Nejd: (TA:) in the dial. of El-Hijáz called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEawaAhinu","text_ar":"العَوَاهِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","As","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}